Short:     Version 1.3 of the simple WB Pacman Game
Uploader:  sebauer@t-online.de (Sebastian Bauer)
Author:    sebauer@t-online.de (Sebastian Bauer)
Type:      game/wb
Kurz:      Version 1.3 des einfachen WB Pacman Spiel
Requires:  OS 3.0
Version:   1.3

Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~
This is simple WB Pacman game which I developed a long time ago. I found
the source on my old HD and I updated it a little bit (also to test my
cpublit.library). However the support of the cpublit.library has been
removed since version 1.2.

Copyright, Distribtion and Disclamer
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
SimplePac is ©1995-2000 by Sebastian Bauer.
SimplePac is freeware. Feel free to spreat it, as long as
all files are included and in an unchanged form. You are not
allowed to make profit from its distribution!
In no way the author can be made responible for any damage created
by the program. Use it at your own risk!

Features
  - WB game
  - Resizable Game Window
  - Supports configurable Sound via Datatypes (but no good sounds are
    included)
  - Highscore List
  - Keyboard and Joystick Support (via lowlevel.library)

History
~~~~~~~
Version 1.3 (15.10.2000)
 - reduced memory usage somewhat
 - fixes crashes with smaller window sizes
   (bug reported by Hynek Schlawack)

Version 1.2 (17.09.2000)
 - rewritten in C and compiled with SAS
 - works now really on graphics cards
 - removed support of the cpublit.library

Version 1.1 (28.06.1998)
 - Speed improvment on GfxCards
 - Include title graphics by Chrisoph Bubel
 - like in the original pac man you can see the points after you have
   eaten a monster
 - some bugs fixed (reported by Luca Longone)
 - possibility to slow down the game
   (suggested by Benjamin Hussong and Christoph Bubel)

Version 1.0 (25.01.1998)
 - initial public release

How can you reach me?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
If you like the game or find some bugs e-mail me. You should also contact me if
you have a good set of pacman sounds and a really good icon.


